        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued November 23 at 3:44PM CST by NWS Midland/Odessa TX</headline>
        <description>At 344 PM CST, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 13
miles west of Goldsmith, or 18 miles northeast of Kermit, moving
northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Notrees.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM CST for
western Texas.</instruction>
